QUALIFICATION: Preoccupied by Titania Meigen, 1800. Hendel (1908) was the first after Meigen (1800) to give characters to differentiate the taxon (reproducing Meigen?s characters) and to treat Titania as valid, which makes the name available from that work with Meigen as author. No species were included in Hendel (1908). The first included species is in Coquillett (1910), who designated Chlorops laeta Meigen, 1803 as the type species. The action of the ICZN (1955) suppressed Titania only for the purpose of priority and not for homonymy. As there is no wording in Opinion 678 (ICZN 1963) to contravene earlier rulings of names in Meigen (1800), this allows for Titania to be made available by subsequent usage as a valid taxon, but the name immediately becomes invalid as a junior homonym of Titania Meigen, 1800
